    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-07-21T16:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-07-21T16:25:00-05:00" n="448"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <head>448. Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d448fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National
                        Security File, Country File, Pakistan, Vol. VII, Memos, 10/66–7/67.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-07-21T17:25:00-04:00">July 21, 1967, 5:25 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. President:</p>
                <p>In the attached, Messrs. <persName corresp="#p_SCL1">Schultze</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_FOL1">Freeman</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_GWS1">Gaud</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d448fn2">Reference is to a July 5 memorandum to the
                        President from <persName corresp="#p_FOL1">Freeman</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_GWS1">Gaud</persName>, and a July 11 memorandum to the
                        President from <persName corresp="#p_SCL1">Schultze</persName>.</note>
                    recommend that you authorize an agreement for one million tons of <gloss
                        target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>–480 wheat for Pakistan. (The agreement would also
                    contain small quantities of tallow, oil, cotton and dry milk.) This wheat was
                    part of the package you approved as our pledge at the May meeting of the
                    Pakistan <gloss target="#t_AID1">Aid</gloss> Consortium.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SCL1">Schultze</persName>’s memorandum (Tab A) gives a
                    good summary of the case for the agreement and the things the Paks have agreed
                    to do in return—including buying most of their commercial wheat purchases from
                    the United States.</p>
                <p>I recommend you approve.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Walt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Approve<note n="3" xml:id="d448fn3">
                            <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> checked this option and
                            added a handwritten notation that reads: “Notify new ambassador
                                <persName corresp="#p_OBHJ1">Oehlert</persName> who is still
                            here.”</note>
                    </p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Disapprove</p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Speak to me</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
